{"title":"Vintage Hand-Drawn VHS Labels","link":"https://kottke.org/24/12/vintage-hand-drawn-vhs-labels","date":1733430352000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1284\" height=\"1263\" alt=\"hand-drawn label on a VHS tape\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1284\" height=\"1222\" alt=\"hand-drawn label on a VHS tape\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/vhs-labels-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1284\" height=\"1268\" alt=\"hand-drawn label on a VHS tape\" /></p>\n\n<p>This person posted <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/VHS/comments/1h3rold/sample_size_of_my_dads_collection_of_hundreds_of/\">a bunch of images of their dad’s old VHS tapes</a> with lovingly hand-drawn labels indicating their contents. Kids, this is what people did before the internet.</p>\n\n<p>Also, it’s weird/interesting that CDs, DVDs, Blu-ray, LaserDisc, cassettes, MiniDisc, and 8-tracks are all played on devices named for the media (e.g. CD player) but VHS tapes are played on VCRs. We could have easily started calling them “VCR tapes” or “VHS players” en masse, but we mostly collectively stuck to the “correct” terminology. (thx, david)</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/design\">design</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/movies\">movies</a></p>\n\n         <p>💬 <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/12/vintage-hand-drawn-vhs-labels\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> →</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"b87f53119a34aa6ca5a6e356a437589e24f83c686d98cf92ec0bd2b213b509fe","category":"Sites"}